  urldate = {2025-06-22},
  abstract = {We introduce a new framework for decomposing the mutual information between a set of source variables and a target variable into nonnegative components representing the unique information from each source, the redundant information shared by multiple sources, and the synergistic information that emerges only from the interaction of multiple sources. This framework is based on a novel measure of shared information that satisfies a set of intuitively desirable axioms. We show that this measure is unique under these axioms, and that it can be computed efficiently for discrete variables. We illustrate the application of this framework to a variety of problems in neuroscience and machine learning, and discuss its implications for understanding information processing in complex systems.},
